issuesFound.explanation:
When the product grid is filtered, the visible‑count badge is updated visually only. No ARIA live region announces the new count, leaving screen‑reader users unaware of how many products are shown.  
  Fix (add a hidden live region in the markup, e.g. `<div id="product-count-status" aria-live="polite" class="sr-only"></div>` and update it):  
  ```js
  function _updateCountBadge(count) {
    if (!_countBadge) return;
    _countBadge.textContent = String(count);
    setAttr(_countBadge, 'aria-label', `${count} product${count !== 1 ? 's' : ''}`);
    // Announce the change
    const status = document.getElementById('product-count-status');
    if (status) status.textContent = `${count} product${count !== 1 ? 's' : ''} displayed`;
  }
  ```

